                                                                                        Threat Detection 3 — Task-Wise Answers

Task 2 — Bruteforce & Detection
• Which attack technique caused a brute-force alert? → Repeated SSH logon failures
• Username targeted in brute force: → svc_user
• IP with repeated login failures: → 10.10.56.12
• Event ID associated with login failure: → 4625

Task 3 — Malware Process Monitoring
• Which process was observed spawning network activity suspiciously? → malproc
• Parent process of suspicious binary: → systemd
• Which port did the suspicious process use mainly? → 8080

Task 4 — Network Beaconing
• Most frequent destination domain seen in outbound connections: → beacon.badhost.org
• Which protocol was used for outbound C2 beaconing: → HTTP
• Most common response code from C2 server: → 200

Task 5 — Correlation & Alerting
• Which correlation rule joined failed login + malware execution?

index=security OR index=sysmon | stats count by src_ip, exe


• What anomalous pattern was revealed:
→ Failed SSH attempts from IP followed by suspicious malproc on same host
• Flag for completing the room: → THM{threat_detected_3_master}
